commit.message:
Update links to the docs/HowTo.md file

According to 99fce10 that renames doc/ to docs/, this commit matches links with
those updates.

And also this commit appends .md file extension and changes the href format as
relative so that we can click it and recognize it as a repository internal link
(same as CONTRIBUTING.md).

Signed-off-by: Yasuhiro Яша Asaka <yasuhiro.asaka@grauwoelfchen.net>

Update links to the docs/HowTo.md file

According to 99fce10 that renames doc/ to docs/, this commit matches links with
those updates.

And also this commit appends .md file extension and changes the href format as
relative so that we can click it and recognize it as a repository internal link
(same as CONTRIBUTING.md).

Signed-off-by: Yasuhiro Яша Asaka <yasuhiro.asaka@grauwoelfchen.net>

commit.message:
Update v3.1 changelog with relevant missing changes

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Add printf format attribute to logit()

Also, silence warning from GCC-11.  It seems to think that ntpc->server
can still be NULL, despite our checking for that before calling run().

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Check resulting ntpc.server before starting, may still be NULL

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Minor, output useage to stderr on error, otherwise stdout

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Ensure adjtimex.1 is always included in dist archive

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Ensure unit file is always included in dist archive

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Restore support for building .deb files from top Makefile

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Add configure summary

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

release-hook: verify proper tag format

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Overhaul release target, drop .deb generation, add .sha256

Update changelogs and bump version for v3.1 release

Drop Travis-CI in favor of GitHub Actions

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Use same error message for same class of problem in code base

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Fix missing argument to printf format specifier, found by Coverity

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Use same variable names across entire code base

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

.github: enaure pkg-config is installed, for detecting systemd .pc

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Update sntpd.service, systemd unit, with correct man page (renamed)

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

debian: explicitly enable systemd support in configure

Trying to isolate why the GitHub Action fails to build the .deb files.
Right now it doesn't seem to find the the unit file.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

.github: mismatch in expectations

Apparently systemd is not installed in the debian:stable container?

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

.github: ensure all dependencies for .deb package are installed

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

.github: add workflows for building/scanning/releasing

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

.github: some pointers for contributors

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Prepare changelogs for v3.1 release

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Update copyright years and co-author's last name

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Retry setup_socket() from main loop() also on bind()/connect() fail

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Let setup_socket() return error, and retry in main loop() instead

If we get SIGTERM while retrying the DNS lookup we would not catch it in
the init/setup phase, only loop() clears the nptc->live flag.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Slightly improved error message when DNS lookup fails

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Call res_init() before retrying getaddrinfo()

When sntpd is started before networking is up we seem to get stuck in an
infinite (?) retry-loop resolving pool.ntp.org.  This patch ensures we
clear the resolver's cache before retrying.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>
